treatment:03FC8787E165FFCBFED3F91A9E9DF8E9
    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172309>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172310>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172312>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172311> ;
    dc:creator "Chisholm, Leslie A.; Whittington, Ian D." ;
    dc:title "Capsaloides perugiai (Setti, 1898) Price 1938, n. syn." ;
    trt:augmentsTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Capsaloides_perugiai_Price_1938> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172308> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172308>
    bibo:endPage "20" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "1160" ;
    dc:creator "Chisholm, Leslie A.; Whittington, Ian D." ;
    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "Revision of Capsaloides (Monogenea: Capsalidae) with a redescription of C. magnaspinosus Price, 1939 from the nasal tissue of Tetrapterus audax (Istiophoridae) collected off Nelson Bay, New South Wales, Australia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172309>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172310>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172312>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172311> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172309>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Haptoral accessory sclerites of Capsaloides species. A. C. cornutus, drawn from USNPC 35136. B. C. cristatus, drawn from USNPC 63597. C. C. hoffmannae, drawn from CNHE 0 0 2718. D. C. magnaspinosus, drawn from USNPC 35648. E. C. nairagi, drawn from USNPC 63599. F. C. perugiai, redrawn from Setti (1898). G. C. sinuatus, redrawn from Goto (1894). Scale bar: 100 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172309/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172310>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Nomarksi photomicrographs of the dorsomarginal body sclerites of Capsaloides species. For consistent comparison, the sclerites were photographed at the level of the anterior border of the ovary. A. C. cornutus, from USNPC 35136. B. C. cristatus, from USNPC 63597. C. C. hoffmannae, from CNHE 002718; note that the cusps of the sclerites cannot be seen well in this unflattened specimen and the body margin appears annulated. D. C. magnaspinosus, from USNPC 35648. E. C. nairagi, from USNPC 63599; note that the sclerites are distributed in a slightly zigzagged pattern. F. C. perugiai, from USNPC 63600 (specimen originally identified as C. tetrapteri). Scale bars: 20 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172312>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Haptoral accessory sclerites of Capsaloides perugiai and those species newly synonymised with C. perugiai. A. C. istiophori, redrawn from Yamaguti (1968). B. C. istiophori, drawn from USNPC 63598. C. C. marielenae, drawn from CNHE 0 0 0 133. D. C. perugiai, redrawn from Setti (1898). D. C. tetrapteri, drawn from USNPC 63600. Note that the only specimen of C. istiophori deposited is large and the morphology of the accessory sclerites are slightly different (B) to that drawn by Yamaguti (1968) (see A) who based his description on 28 specimens. Scale bar: 50 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172311>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Variation in the morphology of the dorsomarginal body sclerites of Capsaloides perugiai and those species (C. istiophori, C. marielenae and C. tetrapteri) newly synonymised with C. perugiai (present study). Note that the number of cusps associated with the crown­shaped sclerite decrease towards the posterior body region. A. C. istiophori, drawn from USNPC 63598. B. C. marielenae, drawn from CNHE 0 0 0 133. C. C. perugiai, redrawn from Setti (1898). D. C. tetrapteri, drawn from USNPC 63600. Scale bar: 10 m." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172311/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

